  "judgment": {
    "summary": "The user asks for a summary of the US Civil Rights Movement and then follows up with questions regarding whether the movement was a linear progression and which tactical approach historians view as most effective. The assistant provides a historical overview, acknowledges internal philosophical divides (nonviolence vs. militancy), and concludes by stating a historical consensus regarding the effectiveness of nonviolent direct action in achieving legislative change.",
